<div><h3>SPAN 138 - Telling Stories Through Fiction and Film </h3>  <hr>Stories can cut across national borders, socioeconomic tensions, and literary and cinematic genres. In this course, students will develop greater fluency in Spanish as they analyze stories (and human characters) that function well when living between the margins.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=98536" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98536&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=98536&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt1629" target="_blank">SPAN 131</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>  or <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=29&coid=99858" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=99858&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=29&coid=99858&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt4189" target="_blank">SPAN 132</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span> or permission; Native speakers welcome.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> LP<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> -<br><br><strong>Placement Guidelines</strong><br> Please visit the <a href="http://www2.clarku.edu/departments/foreign/Undergraduate/placement.cfm">Department of Language, Literature and Culture</a> for the language placement guidelines.<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt1629"></div><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt4189"></div></div>		</td>
